WEBVTT

00:01.687 --> 00:03.812
SHEK: <i>I spilled a lot of
Blackblood that night,</i>

00:03.815 --> 00:06.483
- but not as much as your friend The Wolf.
- Who is this "Wolf"?

00:06.486 --> 00:08.892
SHEK: <i> It's that blacksmith you've
been spending so much time with.</i>

00:08.894 --> 00:11.528
I want to send a letter
to The Worm's supplier.

00:11.530 --> 00:13.014
JANZO: <i>You brought a
Plagueling inside the wall?</i>

00:13.016 --> 00:14.602
What exactly is it that
you want me to figure out?

00:14.604 --> 00:16.876
GARRET: <i>Those are The Bones,
the men who killed your family.</i>

00:16.878 --> 00:19.700
I've written two dispatches to
be delivered to the Prime Order

00:19.703 --> 00:21.434
in the event of my untimely death.

00:21.437 --> 00:25.265
This is our only chance to protect
the Outpost from the Prime Order.

00:25.268 --> 00:26.695
<i>Or should I say "Your Majesty"?</i>

00:26.698 --> 00:28.906
To satisfy the law,
Talon will be executed.

00:28.909 --> 00:31.847
I'll send it back and I'll never open
that door again, just tell me how.

00:31.850 --> 00:34.051
I told you without a
shadow of doubt or fear.

00:34.054 --> 00:37.132
You should never have turned
your back on me, old Wolf.

00:37.135 --> 00:39.088
- [BLADE SINKS IN]
- [GROANS]

00:39.091 --> 00:41.691
- You're good, Blackblood.
- Better than you.

00:41.693 --> 00:43.493
[GRUNTS]

00:51.570 --> 00:53.670
[CHITTERING]

00:55.000 --> 01:01.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:15.714 --> 01:17.647
[SPEAKING BLACKBLOOD] _

01:17.650 --> 01:19.783
[SNARLING]

01:23.414 --> 01:26.046
_

01:31.944 --> 01:34.144
[GRUNTS]

01:34.146 --> 01:36.260
[SNARLING]

01:36.263 --> 01:41.554
_

01:42.898 --> 01:45.888
_

01:45.891 --> 01:47.023
[GRUNTS]

01:52.931 --> 01:54.064
[GROWLING]

01:56.785 --> 01:58.179
It was you.

02:05.277 --> 02:07.610
[SNARLING]

02:09.999 --> 02:12.481
_

02:12.484 --> 02:14.435
[ROARING]

02:14.438 --> 02:16.514
_

02:35.107 --> 02:37.240
[LABORED BREATHING]

02:41.346 --> 02:43.947
The Lu-Qiri?

02:43.949 --> 02:45.415
I sent him back.

02:55.127 --> 02:57.761
Why?

02:57.763 --> 03:01.064
I don't understand.

03:01.066 --> 03:04.131
You are one of the scum
that killed my people,

03:04.134 --> 03:05.733
my family.

03:05.736 --> 03:08.337
Not my finest hour,

03:08.340 --> 03:10.340
but I'm not sorry I did it.

03:10.343 --> 03:12.843
You son of a bitch.

03:12.846 --> 03:15.313
Because if I hadn't been there,

03:15.316 --> 03:17.784
I would never have discovered you.

03:25.957 --> 03:27.724
You're no better than the rest of them.

03:27.726 --> 03:31.961
You're right. I was no better.

03:31.963 --> 03:37.600
But when your Lu-Qiri came
between my arrow and you,

03:37.602 --> 03:40.490
I looked into your little eyes...

03:40.493 --> 03:42.209
I changed.

03:42.212 --> 03:45.514
And since then I've dedicated my life

03:45.517 --> 03:48.881
to studying the prophecies,

03:48.884 --> 03:51.541
searching for understanding

03:51.544 --> 03:54.746
in the hope that I would find you.

03:54.749 --> 03:56.685
You should have told me.

03:56.688 --> 04:01.591
If I had, would you have listened to me?

04:01.593 --> 04:03.726
Or stuck a sword in me?

04:03.728 --> 04:08.698
[COUGHING]

04:08.700 --> 04:10.631
Promise me...

04:10.634 --> 04:13.569
you'll fulfill the prophecy.

04:13.572 --> 04:15.498
I don't even know what the prophecy is.

04:15.501 --> 04:19.302
It's humankind's only hope.

04:19.305 --> 04:21.204
For you,

04:21.208 --> 04:23.342
so you never forget.

04:32.068 --> 04:35.102
Find the Book of Names.

04:35.105 --> 04:38.131
What? The book of what?

04:38.134 --> 04:40.740
The...

04:40.743 --> 04:44.845
No, no, no. Don't die
on me, old bastard.

04:44.848 --> 04:48.583
Find...

04:48.586 --> 04:51.687
You haven't much time.

04:51.690 --> 04:55.192
The Dragman is coming.

04:55.195 --> 04:59.998
The Dragman will find you.

05:00.001 --> 05:01.200
I don't understand.

05:01.203 --> 05:05.739
The Dragman will find you.

05:05.742 --> 05:08.276
Find the Book of Names.

05:08.279 --> 05:09.811
Promise me.

05:19.584 --> 05:21.318
I promise.

05:25.076 --> 05:28.244
<i>[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]</i>

05:28.247 --> 05:32.029
- <font color="#D81D1D">Synced and corrected by VitoSilans</font> -
-- <font color="#138CE9">www.Addic7ed.com</font> --

05:39.658 --> 05:41.791
[HORSE WHINNIES]

05:54.482 --> 05:58.384
Ambassador. To what do I owe the honor?

05:58.386 --> 06:01.354
No need for formalities.

06:01.356 --> 06:02.955
You're Karric Unger,

06:02.957 --> 06:06.426
Acolyte of the Shrine at Cadrian's Pass.

06:06.428 --> 06:08.361
That was many years ago.

06:08.363 --> 06:10.196
I have a family now.

06:10.198 --> 06:13.866
We pay tribute to the
Order every harvest.

06:13.868 --> 06:16.469
And a lovely family it is, too.

06:16.471 --> 06:18.771
I'm searching for the "Vex Rezicon."

06:18.773 --> 06:22.542
The Book of Names? I've never seen it.

06:22.544 --> 06:24.610
It is kept in the Sanctum by the Elders.

06:24.612 --> 06:26.012
The Elders are dead.

06:26.014 --> 06:27.747
When the Greyskins attacked the Shrine,

06:27.749 --> 06:28.881
they killed everyone.

06:28.883 --> 06:30.683
Except you.

06:33.354 --> 06:36.722
- I was out gathering...
- You abandoned your sworn duty.

06:36.724 --> 06:40.793
Relax. All I want is the "Vex."

06:40.795 --> 06:43.496
Is it still in the Shrine?

06:43.498 --> 06:45.665
Perhaps the Greyskins took it.

06:45.667 --> 06:48.334
Or burned it. Who knows?

06:57.912 --> 07:01.481
You don't want me to find
the Book of Names, do you?

07:01.483 --> 07:03.116
I don't know where it is.

07:03.118 --> 07:04.717
I swear to the gods.

07:04.719 --> 07:07.787
- [GASPS]
- You lie to me,

07:07.789 --> 07:10.857
even when you have so much to lose.

07:10.859 --> 07:14.193
- So much.
- I would never lie.

07:14.195 --> 07:16.496
Choose.

07:16.498 --> 07:19.857
What? No! Please!

07:19.860 --> 07:22.935
Choose or I will choose for you.

07:22.937 --> 07:25.638
Me!

07:25.640 --> 07:27.773
I choose me!

07:27.775 --> 07:30.309
I admire the creativity of your choice.

07:30.311 --> 07:33.246
Do not lie to me again.
Where is the book?

07:33.248 --> 07:35.548
It's inside the altar of fire.

07:39.087 --> 07:41.787
- How does one open it?
- I don't know!

07:41.789 --> 07:44.957
They only took it out
once while I was there.

07:44.959 --> 07:48.494
They lit fires and chanted
something, that's all I know!

07:48.497 --> 07:51.564
I swear!

07:51.566 --> 07:55.468
[GASPING]

07:55.470 --> 07:58.237
You should have died with
your brothers at the Shrine.

07:58.239 --> 07:59.839
[DRAWS SWORD]

07:59.841 --> 08:01.007
[GASPING]

08:01.009 --> 08:03.075
Please don't hurt them.

08:05.313 --> 08:07.613
- [GROANS]
- No!

08:07.615 --> 08:10.950
[GROANING]

08:12.519 --> 08:14.312
KARRIC: No! No!

08:14.315 --> 08:16.389
You're a man who watches tragedy unfold

08:16.391 --> 08:17.857
and does nothing to stop it.

08:17.860 --> 08:19.942
This time, it'll be your tragedy.

08:19.945 --> 08:22.161
Please don't! They've done nothing!

08:22.164 --> 08:25.531
Shh. Just watch.

08:25.533 --> 08:27.453
[SOBBING]

08:27.456 --> 08:30.217
When the moon is aflame,

08:30.220 --> 08:32.620
a Blackblood will summon...

08:32.623 --> 08:35.124
the slayers of men,

08:35.126 --> 08:38.530
to conquer and purge...

08:47.848 --> 08:50.416
I can finally get
back to you, my friend.

08:50.419 --> 08:53.586
<i>[MUSIC PLAYING]</i>

09:12.086 --> 09:13.218
Hmm.

09:21.795 --> 09:25.051
[FLIES BUZZING]

09:25.054 --> 09:26.432
[CHUCKLES]

09:28.067 --> 09:30.535
It's fascinating.

09:30.538 --> 09:33.706
<i>[MUSIC PLAYING]</i>

09:48.003 --> 09:52.005
"The moon is a flame, a Blackblood
will summon the slayers of men,

09:52.007 --> 09:55.098
to conquer and purge
the oppressors of old."

09:57.279 --> 09:59.679
Even in death, you nag me.

09:59.681 --> 10:01.815
[SIGHS]

10:14.529 --> 10:16.663
[SIGHS]

10:17.566 --> 10:20.834
"Find it," you said,

10:20.836 --> 10:22.817
not "Get it off the shelf."

10:24.473 --> 10:26.339
Never made anything easy, did you?

10:26.341 --> 10:28.007
[MUTTERS]

10:28.009 --> 10:30.376
- [EXHALES SHARPLY]
- Didn't mean to startle you.

10:30.378 --> 10:33.980
When you sneak up on someone
without announcing, it startles them.

10:35.684 --> 10:40.553
I, um, I heard Shek killed the smith.

10:40.555 --> 10:42.555
Terribly sorry.

10:42.557 --> 10:44.824
I know how close he was to you.

10:44.826 --> 10:47.560
He was the Bones I was looking for.

10:47.562 --> 10:49.332
What?

10:49.335 --> 10:50.768
He has the mark?

10:59.207 --> 11:02.375
Would you like help
disposing of the body?

11:02.377 --> 11:06.513
No. I'm going to bury him myself.

11:06.515 --> 11:08.081
Okay.

11:11.086 --> 11:13.753
You doing some reading?

11:13.755 --> 11:16.222
I can't.

11:16.224 --> 11:18.275
It's all written in this weird language.

11:18.278 --> 11:20.478
- That's Yindrian.
- Of course it is.

11:20.481 --> 11:23.296
No, it is. I can read...
Well, parts of it.

11:23.298 --> 11:26.533
I can actually read and write
12 different tongues, but, um,

11:26.535 --> 11:28.401
I can only really speak three.

11:28.403 --> 11:29.969
You're amazing.

11:29.971 --> 11:31.793
[CHUCKLES]

11:31.796 --> 11:33.195
Do you really mean that?

11:35.210 --> 11:38.488
I'm, um, I'm a little
rusty on Yindrian, actually,

11:38.491 --> 11:40.380
since, uh, no one speaks it,

11:40.382 --> 11:43.716
Yindrians all being
slaughtered by the Prime Order.

11:43.718 --> 11:46.186
- They're all dead?
- Hm, just like your people.

11:48.890 --> 11:50.957
I'm sorry. That was
very insensitive of me.

11:50.959 --> 11:52.325
Why?

11:52.327 --> 11:55.028
Just reminding you about
another awful genocide.

11:55.030 --> 11:56.121
It was horrible, I'm sorry.

11:56.124 --> 11:58.531
Why would the Prime
Order wipe them out?

11:58.533 --> 12:00.333
Oh.

12:00.335 --> 12:02.235
Well, I guess most ancient prophecies

12:02.237 --> 12:04.204
were written in their native tongue.

12:04.206 --> 12:06.239
So if there's no one left
to translate them, well,

12:06.241 --> 12:10.176
the Prime Order can interpret
the texts however they wish.

12:10.178 --> 12:12.078
It's a wonderful language, by the way.

12:12.080 --> 12:14.347
I could just sit here
and read it for days.

12:14.349 --> 12:17.617
It's just so colorful and interesting.

12:17.619 --> 12:21.754
Did you know that in Yindrian
there's 20 different words for "sky"?

12:21.756 --> 12:25.291
Well, knock yourself out. You
can read everything in the room.

12:25.293 --> 12:28.361
Really? You don't mind?

12:28.363 --> 12:31.464
Just keep your eyes open for
something called the Book of Names.

12:31.466 --> 12:34.167
The Book of Names?

12:34.169 --> 12:35.802
Okay.

12:35.804 --> 12:37.770
Why?

12:37.772 --> 12:41.274
I promised the smith I would find it.

12:41.276 --> 12:43.243
He made it sound very important.

12:45.280 --> 12:46.631
There you are, Janzo.

12:46.634 --> 12:48.159
Been looking all over for you.

12:48.162 --> 12:51.150
- Why?
- Good news.

12:51.152 --> 12:53.553
Mistress said the bird came.

12:53.555 --> 12:56.222
It's not good news, Munt.

12:56.224 --> 12:57.924
Not for me, anyway.

12:59.160 --> 13:01.527
Hold that thought. I'll be right back.

13:08.103 --> 13:11.304
[DOOR CLOSES]

13:11.306 --> 13:13.928
Yes? You sent for me.

13:17.312 --> 13:21.180
Commander Calkussar
says the time has come.

13:21.182 --> 13:23.683
Today I'll be introduced
to the encampment.

13:23.685 --> 13:25.718
What, now?

13:25.720 --> 13:29.522
We've only just properly
begun their training.

13:29.524 --> 13:31.324
We dare not wait any longer.

13:31.327 --> 13:33.660
You're Prime Order gross suspicious.

13:35.497 --> 13:38.598
I heard about Talon,

13:38.600 --> 13:39.899
that she survived.

13:39.901 --> 13:42.702
[CHUCKLES] Yes.

13:45.407 --> 13:47.240
Did you intervene?

13:48.743 --> 13:50.677
No.

13:50.679 --> 13:54.614
No, I would never do that
without your orders to do so.

13:54.616 --> 13:56.082
Then how?

13:58.887 --> 14:01.954
It's complicated.

14:01.956 --> 14:06.125
But, um, there is
something you should know...

14:06.127 --> 14:08.261
about Talon.

14:10.432 --> 14:13.032
Go on.

14:13.034 --> 14:14.801
I know what you're going to say.

14:14.803 --> 14:16.836
You do?

14:16.838 --> 14:19.739
- Talon can summon demons.
- You're in love with Talon.

14:19.741 --> 14:21.662
BOTH: What?

14:24.112 --> 14:26.412
Where have you been,
boy? My man on the wall

14:26.414 --> 14:28.147
saw the birds fly in before midday.

14:28.149 --> 14:29.733
Couldn't believe it myself.

14:35.590 --> 14:37.256
"Gallows Rock.

14:37.258 --> 14:40.225
Sundown, before dark moon.

14:40.228 --> 14:42.162
Bring all gold."

14:42.165 --> 14:44.999
- "Before dark moon"? That's...
- That's tomorrow night.

14:45.002 --> 14:48.468
[LAUGHING] Tomorrow
night? That's so exciting!

14:48.470 --> 14:50.002
Ow!

14:50.004 --> 14:51.971
You shouldn't be excited.

14:51.973 --> 14:54.307
You should be terrified.

14:54.309 --> 14:56.242
Gallows Rock is where bad things happen.

14:56.244 --> 14:58.244
You could be dealing with
the Nordejori bandits,

14:58.246 --> 15:00.246
or even the Denalese smugglers.

15:00.248 --> 15:02.473
You're good with words. You'll
talk your way out of any problem.

15:02.475 --> 15:05.118
What? Me? No, no, no, absolutely not.

15:05.120 --> 15:07.019
I am way... [GROANS]

15:07.021 --> 15:09.021
I am way too busy.

15:09.023 --> 15:11.391
[STAMMERING] I'm helping
Captain Garret Spears

15:11.393 --> 15:13.092
with a Plagueling problem and...

15:13.094 --> 15:15.361
And I'm helping dear
Talon translate some...

15:15.363 --> 15:19.031
Captain Spears and that girl are more
important to you than your mother?

15:19.033 --> 15:21.801
No, of course not. But, oh, Mum,

15:21.803 --> 15:24.003
on the way to Gallows
Rock are the Plaguelings,

15:24.005 --> 15:26.653
not to mention that the bandits are
probably the ones selling the stuff.

15:26.655 --> 15:28.808
Either way, I'm going to be dead.

15:28.810 --> 15:31.844
- Munt will look after you.
- No.

15:34.482 --> 15:35.615
No?

15:36.851 --> 15:39.452
No?

15:39.454 --> 15:42.155
After everything I've done for you?

15:42.157 --> 15:45.792
You ungrateful little twit!

15:45.794 --> 15:48.060
Mother, I have done everything
you have ever asked for,

15:48.062 --> 15:51.397
right or wrong, but this time you're
going to have to find somebody else.

15:51.399 --> 15:52.999
There isn't anybody else!

15:53.001 --> 15:55.983
Bill's dead, and Munt's a halfwit!

16:01.976 --> 16:04.477
- Munt will look after you.
- [CHUCKLES]

16:04.479 --> 16:07.413
Munt would have me dead
if it came down to it.

16:07.415 --> 16:09.782
You listen to me.

16:09.784 --> 16:11.684
I'm the one who took you in.

16:11.686 --> 16:13.453
I fed you, I clothed you,

16:13.455 --> 16:15.888
I raised you as my own.

16:15.890 --> 16:20.660
And I can put your little ass back out
on the street again any time I want.

16:20.662 --> 16:22.929
I appreciate what you're saying.

16:22.931 --> 16:27.033
I just believe that going into the
colipsum trade so big is a grave mistake.

16:27.035 --> 16:30.303
I've made a lot of grave
mistakes in my life.

16:30.305 --> 16:31.871
Don't you be one of them.

16:43.985 --> 16:46.819
You caused nothing but pain
and suffering in my life...

16:50.024 --> 16:52.425
but I'm gonna miss you, old man.

16:58.399 --> 17:02.735
Well, I suppose it's one
less body I have to clean up.

17:04.539 --> 17:07.573
There's one in the nightshade,
three more in the sewer.

17:07.575 --> 17:10.209
And one more in the street.

17:10.211 --> 17:13.112
Had a busy night.

17:13.114 --> 17:16.315
All the Bones are dead.

17:16.317 --> 17:18.550
The Lu-Qiri's gone..

17:18.553 --> 17:21.420
You won't have any more trouble from me.

17:21.422 --> 17:23.623
I'll leave the Outpost as agreed.

17:24.893 --> 17:29.829
Good, but, uh, before I escort you out,

17:29.831 --> 17:32.768
Lady Calkussar requests your presence.

17:50.803 --> 17:52.569
Here she is.

17:53.873 --> 17:55.973
Still alive, as it happens.

17:55.975 --> 17:57.908
Marshal, wait outside.

17:57.910 --> 17:59.476
This doesn't concern you.

18:15.628 --> 18:17.261
Talon...

18:19.331 --> 18:20.998
we have so much to talk about.

18:21.000 --> 18:23.776
Start with how you decide
to let Wythers take my head.

18:23.779 --> 18:26.837
It was not a decision
that I made lightly.

18:26.839 --> 18:28.839
At the time, I could see no other way.

18:28.841 --> 18:32.643
Than to save your own
skin. I understand.

18:32.645 --> 18:36.747
Are we done here? I have
to be gone by sundown.

18:36.749 --> 18:40.484
Wythers blackmailed me to get to you.

18:40.486 --> 18:43.053
I hated myself for what I did.

18:44.557 --> 18:48.392
Please, I wish you to stay.

18:50.763 --> 18:54.398
Help me overthrow the Prime Order.

18:54.400 --> 18:57.034
What?

18:57.036 --> 18:59.203
Is that why you want me here?

18:59.205 --> 19:01.038
To help you commit treason?

19:01.040 --> 19:04.675
Just stop letting your
tongue run wild and listen.

19:04.677 --> 19:09.162
My name is not Gwynn, and Commander
Calkussar is not my father.

19:11.062 --> 19:14.117
I am Rosmund, daughter of King Ranulf,

19:14.120 --> 19:16.820
which makes me heir to the Realm.

19:21.460 --> 19:23.460
So let's say I believe you.

19:23.462 --> 19:26.130
What do I do now? Am
I supposed to kneel?

19:26.132 --> 19:30.200
No. No, not at all.

19:30.202 --> 19:32.069
I hope that we can still be friends.

19:32.071 --> 19:35.072
Yes, well, we can always hope.

19:35.074 --> 19:37.975
And I'm hoping that
you'll join our cause.

19:37.977 --> 19:41.578
What can a few hundred men at the
Outpost do against the Prime Order?

19:43.515 --> 19:47.116
We have more men than you think.

19:47.119 --> 19:50.087
And with your help, Talon,
we'll have more than just men.

19:50.089 --> 19:52.256
You'll have men, plus a woman.

19:54.103 --> 19:55.969
Tell me of this demon.

19:58.097 --> 20:00.063
So does everyone know about that now?

20:00.065 --> 20:02.399
Only those who need to know.

20:04.185 --> 20:09.239
The demon is gone. I sent
it back where it belongs.

20:09.241 --> 20:12.873
Well, tell me more.
I want to understand.

20:12.876 --> 20:15.279
Are there more than one such creature?

20:15.281 --> 20:19.583
So I've been told, but
I only have one name.

20:19.585 --> 20:22.381
It's how I summon them, by its name.

20:22.384 --> 20:23.775
Well, then you need to find more.

20:23.778 --> 20:25.254
How did you find the first one?

20:25.257 --> 20:28.225
The smith, but he's dead now.

20:31.397 --> 20:34.264
- The Book of Names.
- What?

20:34.266 --> 20:35.866
I have to go.

20:35.868 --> 20:38.202
But you'll stay here?

20:38.204 --> 20:39.603
At the Outpost?

20:39.605 --> 20:41.303
For now.

20:50.416 --> 20:52.716
We're done here. Stop reading.

20:52.718 --> 20:54.151
I'm just getting started.

20:54.153 --> 20:56.224
And I've already
learned so much already.

20:56.227 --> 20:58.488
- Why don't you want to know?
- Because I think the Book of Names

20:58.490 --> 21:01.295
- is actually a book full of...
- Full of demon names?

21:06.465 --> 21:09.733
You see, I've been
doing some reading now.

21:09.735 --> 21:13.370
You do have black blood, don't you?

21:13.372 --> 21:16.406
Hmm? You see, I'm sure
I read somewhere in here

21:16.408 --> 21:19.784
something about the black
blood summoning the Lu-Qiri...

21:19.787 --> 21:22.579
Oh, Lu-Qiri is a
different name for demon.

21:22.581 --> 21:24.514
I know what a Lu-Qiri is, Janzo.

21:24.516 --> 21:26.842
'Cause that's what
stabbed you, isn't it? Hmm?

21:26.845 --> 21:29.870
The Lu-Qiri? You're basically a witch.

21:29.873 --> 21:32.022
[LAUGHS] And... and if you...

21:32.024 --> 21:34.891
If you had access to all
of these demon names, well,

21:34.893 --> 21:37.594
you could just summon
up a whole army of them.

21:37.596 --> 21:39.830
And that is precisely
why we're not doing this.

21:39.832 --> 21:41.665
Not this one.

21:41.667 --> 21:44.434
- Give it to me, Janzo.
- You made a promise to the smith

21:44.436 --> 21:47.092
that you would find the Book of Names.

21:47.095 --> 21:49.462
- It's not that simple.
- Oh?

21:49.465 --> 21:51.615
Not as simple as sticking to your word

21:51.618 --> 21:53.870
and carrying out the
smith's last dying wish?

21:53.873 --> 21:56.113
Oh, shut up.

21:56.115 --> 22:00.050
Look, even if you did
find the Book of Names,

22:00.052 --> 22:04.021
it doesn't mean that you have to use it.

22:04.023 --> 22:06.223
I don't think I'll be able to find it.

22:06.225 --> 22:11.128
And I... I don't know how to
speak or read "Yindarian" and...

22:11.130 --> 22:13.279
Yindrian.

22:13.376 --> 22:14.775
Yindrian.

22:17.469 --> 22:19.153
I can only look at the pictures.

22:19.156 --> 22:21.438
It's not a problem. I already told you

22:21.440 --> 22:23.121
I will sit here for days

22:23.124 --> 22:25.258
and read through all of
these books just for you.

22:27.572 --> 22:29.712
Why are you always so nice to me, Janzo?

22:29.715 --> 22:32.182
[CHUCKLES]

22:32.184 --> 22:35.485
I just like being around
somebody like you, that's all.

22:35.487 --> 22:40.357
I find your life to be
interesting and thrilling.

22:40.359 --> 22:44.561
Also, I kind of need a
little small favor in return.

22:47.299 --> 22:49.099
What kind of favor?

22:49.101 --> 22:52.502
Well, you see, I'm... I'm
going traveling for a few days

22:52.504 --> 22:56.306
and to deliver some stuff,
and I need a travel companion.

22:56.308 --> 23:00.344
You know, somebody to talk to
and... and help me carry the stuff.

23:00.346 --> 23:02.112
Well, it's not a little favor, is it?

23:02.114 --> 23:06.283
Oh, right.

23:06.285 --> 23:10.426
I suppose neither is translating
all of these books and papers.

23:14.360 --> 23:15.856
Will you come with me?

23:15.859 --> 23:17.961
The smith said I need
to find the Book of Names

23:17.963 --> 23:21.064
before something called
the Dragman finds me.

23:21.066 --> 23:22.733
"Before the Dragman finds you"?

23:22.735 --> 23:24.234
Mm-hmm.

23:26.004 --> 23:27.104
Why?

23:28.640 --> 23:30.481
Is there something you know about it?

23:30.484 --> 23:32.284
No.

23:32.287 --> 23:34.020
Then why are you acting weird?

23:34.023 --> 23:38.292
Just in Yindrian, there's
a word, <i>Drogemane...</i>

23:38.295 --> 23:40.684
- Which means?
- "Death."

23:40.686 --> 23:42.332
Death?

23:44.323 --> 23:46.723
Maybe. Maybe not.

23:46.725 --> 23:48.892
Come on, pick up two or
three of these books and, um,

23:48.894 --> 23:50.494
we can help solve your
problem along the way.

23:50.496 --> 23:52.754
- I don't know.
- Talon,

23:52.757 --> 23:55.632
if you don't come with
me, I may not survive.

23:55.634 --> 23:58.301
Then who's going to translate
all of these books for you, hmm?

24:00.205 --> 24:04.107
So the truth is you don't actually
want me there for my company, do you?

24:04.109 --> 24:05.242
You want my protection.

24:05.244 --> 24:06.977
Pretty much. [CHUCKLES]

24:06.979 --> 24:09.012
And also there might be some...

24:09.014 --> 24:11.681
Some Plaguelings and...
And bandits along the way.

24:11.683 --> 24:13.717
But it'll be really
fun. Come on, let's go.

24:19.702 --> 24:21.707
These men you've gathered,

24:21.709 --> 24:24.076
how do you know they're
going to rally for our cause?

24:24.078 --> 24:26.411
Common men aren't
concerned about causes.

24:26.413 --> 24:28.174
They're about their own
necks, their next meal,

24:28.175 --> 24:29.581
and the safety of their loved ones,

24:29.583 --> 24:31.049
probably in that order.

24:31.051 --> 24:32.651
We'll promise them all three.

24:32.653 --> 24:35.038
You have a low opinion
of the common man.

24:37.091 --> 24:38.523
Halt.

24:38.526 --> 24:41.293
They must be on their way to the
Outpost for the late shipment.

24:41.295 --> 24:43.562
Or because of Magmoor.

24:45.533 --> 24:46.665
Hail!

24:47.672 --> 24:49.372
We've got 20 score swords in the wagon.

24:49.375 --> 24:51.069
We can't afford to lose them.

24:51.072 --> 24:53.238
- Not now.
- I'll take care of this.

24:53.241 --> 24:57.510
Anything happens, protect
Gwynn at all costs.

24:57.513 --> 24:59.713
Come on. [CLICKS TONGUE]

25:11.025 --> 25:14.626
[CHUCKLES] Captain McNor.

25:14.628 --> 25:17.663
Spears. Been a long time.

25:17.665 --> 25:20.933
Indeed. What are you
doing all the way out here?

25:20.935 --> 25:23.869
We're just about to break camp
for our final leg to the Outpost

25:23.871 --> 25:26.921
to collect that shipment
of armaments you owe us.

25:26.924 --> 25:28.774
And here you come with it.

25:28.776 --> 25:30.351
It's better late than never, eh?

25:30.354 --> 25:31.991
Listen, don't worry about the shipment.

25:31.994 --> 25:34.143
We'll take it the rest of
the way to Eckly Station.

25:34.146 --> 25:36.715
Nonsense. We'll take it from here.

25:36.717 --> 25:38.951
I have very direct orders
to accompany the shipment...

25:38.953 --> 25:42.921
And I have remanded
those orders, Captain.

25:42.923 --> 25:46.491
Do you have the relinquishment
papers and inventories?

25:46.494 --> 25:48.828
Of course.

25:58.372 --> 26:00.939
Right here.

26:00.941 --> 26:04.109
<i>[MUSIC PLAYING]</i>

26:07.448 --> 26:10.582
[ALL GRUNTING]

26:36.477 --> 26:38.802
- Help him.
- Come on, yah!

26:43.884 --> 26:45.017
Yah!

26:45.019 --> 26:47.152
[GRUNTING]

26:50.524 --> 26:52.057
[HORSE WHINNIES]

26:54.194 --> 26:55.327
Aah!

26:58.399 --> 27:00.065
Gwynn!

27:01.602 --> 27:03.735
[GRUNTING]

27:07.618 --> 27:09.417
Yah! Yah! Yah!

27:14.114 --> 27:16.099
Garret!

27:16.102 --> 27:17.234
Yah!

27:19.053 --> 27:21.427
- Yah! Yah!
- Yah!

27:29.863 --> 27:31.763
Yah!

27:31.765 --> 27:33.899
[GRUNTING]

27:39.707 --> 27:40.839
Aah!

27:48.949 --> 27:50.182
Garret!

27:54.755 --> 27:55.887
Yah! Yah!

28:09.737 --> 28:11.349
Are you all right?

28:17.511 --> 28:19.644
[PANTING]

28:36.023 --> 28:39.091
Looks like the Commander still
has some fight left in him.

28:47.521 --> 28:50.723
I think it's about time you tell
me what's really in the barrels.

28:50.725 --> 28:54.126
I know you didn't bring me
out this far to deliver wine.

28:54.128 --> 28:56.829
I suppose you do have a right to know.

28:56.831 --> 29:00.332
So, we are going to Gallows Rock

29:00.334 --> 29:02.234
to buy an undisclosed volume

29:02.236 --> 29:05.304
of raw colipsum from an unknown seller.

29:08.042 --> 29:09.508
So what's in those barrels?

29:09.510 --> 29:13.378
Gold. A small fortune in gold.

29:13.380 --> 29:15.885
I should kill you and take
that gold, you stupid idiot.

29:15.888 --> 29:18.550
- [CHUCKLES]
- You know whoever you're meeting up there

29:18.552 --> 29:21.253
is planning to kill
you and take that gold.

29:21.255 --> 29:23.722
What makes you so sure?

29:23.724 --> 29:26.058
So where is this Gallows Rock, anyway?

29:26.060 --> 29:28.660
It's on the high mountain road.

29:28.662 --> 29:30.950
It's a shame, really,
'cause it's so beautiful.

29:30.953 --> 29:32.865
But ever since the upper
mines dried up, well,

29:32.867 --> 29:35.367
no one really goes there anymore.

29:35.369 --> 29:37.903
No one really goes that way, anymore?

29:37.905 --> 29:39.416
Are you listening to yourself?

29:39.419 --> 29:41.507
Listen, I told you it was dangerous.

29:41.509 --> 29:44.176
The Mistress has finally done you in.

29:44.178 --> 29:46.779
Are you even sure there's gold
in those barrels and not rocks?

29:46.781 --> 29:48.981
[SCOFFS] Yeah, of course I'm sure.

29:58.306 --> 29:59.906
There, you see?

30:04.365 --> 30:07.266
- I'm taking my share before we get robbed.
- Uh, share?

30:07.268 --> 30:09.001
Who said anything about a share?

30:09.003 --> 30:12.504
No, no, no. You are here in
exchange for reading your books.

30:12.506 --> 30:14.942
You won't be reading
anything when you're dead.

30:16.377 --> 30:18.127
Do you really think
I'm going to be dead?

30:18.130 --> 30:20.813
I'll try to not let that happen.

30:20.815 --> 30:23.348
This is just insurance.

30:23.350 --> 30:25.994
Excuse me, I'm going to need
those coins to trade the colipsum.

30:25.997 --> 30:28.754
I'm almost certain they're
not going to count every coin.

30:30.558 --> 30:32.291
Come on.

30:32.293 --> 30:34.693
We're leaving the cart here.

30:34.695 --> 30:37.529
- Why?
- Short cut. It'll save us half a day.

30:37.531 --> 30:39.431
Come on, help me.

30:39.433 --> 30:41.033
Help me.

30:46.440 --> 30:50.442
- There's so many.
- This is only the beginning.

30:50.444 --> 30:53.612
When people find out
about you and who you are,

30:53.614 --> 30:57.549
men will flock to your banners.

30:57.551 --> 30:59.398
I've done nothing to deserve their loyalty

30:59.399 --> 31:01.026
except be born to the right parents.

31:01.028 --> 31:04.156
Which means the gods are in your blood.

31:04.158 --> 31:05.991
You were put in this world

31:05.993 --> 31:07.966
to make things right again.

31:10.097 --> 31:12.798
I don't know if I can do that.

31:12.800 --> 31:17.002
You must try. Your whole
life has led to this moment.

31:17.004 --> 31:21.506
Otherwise, the real Gwynn,

31:21.508 --> 31:23.475
she gave her life for naught.

31:25.546 --> 31:27.880
[SIGHS]

31:27.882 --> 31:31.350
Then it's time I fulfill
my father's promise.

31:31.352 --> 31:33.018
Both my fathers.

31:39.393 --> 31:41.693
JANZO: This is the
furthest I've ever been.

31:41.695 --> 31:43.662
How about you?

31:43.664 --> 31:46.105
I've pretty much been everywhere.

31:46.108 --> 31:47.599
Been to the capital?

31:47.601 --> 31:51.670
No. Wouldn't last long there.

31:51.672 --> 31:56.074
The Covenant controls everything
from the roads to the markets.

31:56.076 --> 32:00.512
There's no gambling, no
fighting, no drinking.

32:00.514 --> 32:02.457
I've heard it's quite immaculate.

32:02.460 --> 32:05.716
The walls are meant to be
covered in pure white marble.

32:05.719 --> 32:10.055
And... and the towers, they
have this gold trim around them.

32:10.057 --> 32:11.757
I've always want to see it.

32:11.759 --> 32:15.294
It's all a show to hide
the evil that's inside.

32:15.296 --> 32:18.785
They're all murderers,
every single one of them.

32:22.676 --> 32:24.415
Just nod your head and keep walking.

32:24.418 --> 32:27.105
If you stop, they'll expect something.

32:27.107 --> 32:29.207
A song for the lady and her companion?

32:31.779 --> 32:37.582
♪ I met a fair lady
with hair like the sun ♪

32:37.584 --> 32:41.688
♪ Her eyes were like
moonbeams, lips second to none ♪

32:41.691 --> 32:43.021
[SMOOCHES]

32:43.023 --> 32:44.990
♪ She had castles of gold ♪

32:44.992 --> 32:48.293
- ♪ And she's great in the sack ♪
- [LAUGHING]

32:48.295 --> 32:53.799
♪ But the only thing wrong
was the hump on her back ♪

32:53.801 --> 32:57.836
♪ Yes, the hump on her
back, the hump on her back ♪

32:57.838 --> 33:01.440
♪ The girl of my dreams
has a hump on her back ♪

33:01.442 --> 33:07.679
♪ I could drape her in pearls
but it won't change the fact ♪

33:07.681 --> 33:10.079
♪ That the woman I love ♪

33:10.082 --> 33:15.821
♪ Has a hump on her back ♪

33:15.823 --> 33:18.611
- Oh, absolutely. Take a little bit of money.
- Perfect, I'll take that.

33:18.613 --> 33:21.093
- Put that right here.
- Hey, what about me?

33:21.095 --> 33:22.961
To be fair, the song was half mine.

33:22.963 --> 33:25.430
Well, I don't really have much.

33:25.432 --> 33:27.954
- What about this? Come on, share.
- No. No!

33:27.957 --> 33:31.603
- Share. Now don't you want to share?
- No.

33:31.605 --> 33:34.406
Oh, holding out on us, aren't you?

33:36.105 --> 33:37.277
[GRUNTS]

33:37.280 --> 33:40.278
Looks like the price of
our song just went up.

33:40.280 --> 33:42.180
Off with that pack now, rich boy.

33:42.182 --> 33:44.941
Yours too, my fine, fine lady.

33:44.944 --> 33:48.452
- It's not our money.
- Oh, it's not your money?

33:48.455 --> 33:50.258
[SCOFFS] I couldn't agree more.

33:50.261 --> 33:52.891
[LAUGHS] Good one, sis.

33:52.893 --> 33:55.127
Now here's a tasty thing.

33:55.129 --> 33:58.363
I'm thinking you're going to
take off more than just that pack.

33:58.365 --> 34:01.266
Why don't you take off
them heavy clothes, too?

34:01.268 --> 34:03.735
How much is it worth to you?

34:03.737 --> 34:05.670
Huh? Aah!

34:05.672 --> 34:07.805
[SCREAMING] Ow! Ow!

34:07.808 --> 34:09.574
[GRUNTS]

34:10.476 --> 34:11.610
[GRUNTS]

34:13.313 --> 34:15.147
TALON: Janzo. duck!

34:15.149 --> 34:17.349
[GRUNTING]

34:17.351 --> 34:18.617
Aah!

34:23.409 --> 34:25.524
Don't leave me, you witch!

34:25.525 --> 34:27.125
Ah.

34:27.127 --> 34:29.737
As I said, how much is it worth to you?

34:29.741 --> 34:32.400
Please, I didn't mean anything
by what I said earlier.

34:32.404 --> 34:34.337
Please! Ow! It was just a little joke!

34:34.340 --> 34:36.635
How much is this little
joke worth to you?

34:36.637 --> 34:38.347
We should go.

34:38.350 --> 34:40.304
Y... yes, please! Listen to your man.

34:40.306 --> 34:42.679
- He's not my man.
- Then your lover?

34:42.683 --> 34:44.543
[SCOFFS] I wish!

34:44.545 --> 34:46.844
Sorry. I wish that we
could stay and chat,

34:46.847 --> 34:49.581
but, um, well, we've really
got still a long way to go.

34:49.583 --> 34:52.837
Please, just show mercy. You've
already broken my arm and my leg.

34:52.840 --> 34:57.355
And you don't think I should break
just one more very little thing?

34:57.357 --> 34:59.769
- BOTH: No!
- I don't.

35:05.599 --> 35:08.100
You're lucky my lover has
such a forgiving nature.

35:08.102 --> 35:09.868
Yes, thank you.

35:09.870 --> 35:11.870
I'll just go back to my music.

35:12.736 --> 35:14.336
Thanks, mate.

35:17.778 --> 35:18.910
Lover?

35:20.681 --> 35:23.815
Next time when I say, "Keep
walking," keep walking.

35:23.817 --> 35:27.063
Sorry. It's just that their music
is ever so catchy, you must admit.

35:27.066 --> 35:28.920
You better start translating.

35:28.922 --> 35:32.524
I have a feeling you're not going
to make it back to the Outpost.

35:32.526 --> 35:35.227
Really? [WHIMPERS]

35:37.699 --> 35:40.871
For as long as they have
been Greyskins and humans,

35:40.874 --> 35:42.928
we've been at war.

35:42.931 --> 35:45.179
They are our mortal enemies.

35:45.181 --> 35:48.683
How many of you have lost a
loved one in the Border Wars?

35:48.685 --> 35:51.352
How many have lost a father or a brother

35:51.354 --> 35:54.878
or a son to those filthy Greyskins?

35:54.881 --> 35:57.749
Now let me ask you this...

35:57.752 --> 36:02.154
who has lost a loved one at
the hands of the Prime Order?

36:07.237 --> 36:09.904
No one?

36:09.906 --> 36:13.107
Do you live in such
fear of the Prime Order

36:13.109 --> 36:16.177
that you will not honor the
memory of your loved ones?

36:19.115 --> 36:21.983
They slit my mother's throat

36:21.985 --> 36:26.888
for refusing the advances
of a Covenant officer.

36:26.890 --> 36:29.357
I was four years old,

36:29.359 --> 36:31.526
but I'll never forget.

36:32.896 --> 36:34.228
Who else?

36:34.230 --> 36:36.696
Who among you has seen a loved one

36:36.699 --> 36:40.535
put to death for speaking
out against tyranny?

36:43.173 --> 36:47.475
Who among you has witnessed murder,

36:47.477 --> 36:49.510
rape, or plunder

36:49.512 --> 36:52.046
at the hands of the
Prime Order soldiers?

36:54.384 --> 36:58.653
Yes, the Greyskins are and
always will be our enemy.

37:00.190 --> 37:03.758
But our greatest enemy walks among us.

37:03.760 --> 37:06.627
It wears red armor...

37:06.629 --> 37:09.864
stained with the blood of our families.

37:09.866 --> 37:12.700
MAN: You're the betrayer!

37:12.702 --> 37:16.504
Yes, they call me the Betrayer.

37:18.942 --> 37:22.377
I opened the palace gates.

37:22.379 --> 37:27.582
I stood by as the queen
mother was beheaded

37:27.584 --> 37:30.284
and then King Ranulf himself.

37:30.286 --> 37:33.688
But all this I did
by the king's command.

37:35.392 --> 37:39.360
It was all part of a desperate plan.

37:39.362 --> 37:42.296
Sacrifice many...

37:42.298 --> 37:44.432
to save one.

37:46.936 --> 37:48.836
I stood by...

37:48.838 --> 37:52.306
as my own daughter, Gwynn, was beheaded

37:52.308 --> 37:55.877
in place of Princess Rosmund.

37:55.879 --> 37:59.781
Today marks the culmination
of the king's plan.

37:59.783 --> 38:04.218
Gentlemen, the time has
now come for you to bow down

38:04.220 --> 38:07.222
before your queen,

38:07.225 --> 38:09.125
Queen Rosmund.

38:15.550 --> 38:17.799
Bow before your queen.

38:17.801 --> 38:21.636
MAN: Why should we believe
you? She could be anyone.

38:21.638 --> 38:23.727
How dare you question me!

38:23.730 --> 38:24.972
Commander.

38:26.810 --> 38:28.472
Take me forward.

38:31.247 --> 38:35.283
Who among you has been to the Capital?

38:35.285 --> 38:37.613
Who has seen my mother,
Queen Annessandra,

38:37.616 --> 38:40.283
before she was murdered
by the Prime Order?

38:42.192 --> 38:43.458
You.

38:43.460 --> 38:46.327
Gwynn, don't.

38:46.329 --> 38:47.962
I remember you.

38:49.699 --> 38:53.267
I worked in the royal gardens.

38:53.269 --> 38:56.103
Yes. Danomar, of course.

38:56.105 --> 38:58.773
And you always caught me
picking your best roses.

39:01.144 --> 39:03.110
And you, sir,

39:03.112 --> 39:05.847
you have a familiar face as well.

39:05.849 --> 39:07.548
I tended the stables.

39:07.550 --> 39:11.319
Yes, of course. Grumman, is it?

39:11.321 --> 39:13.254
It's Gulman.

39:15.091 --> 39:19.160
It's as though the
queen herself were alive.

39:19.162 --> 39:22.763
Princess Rosmund?

39:27.737 --> 39:29.511
You may rise.

39:35.011 --> 39:37.011
[LAUGHING]

39:37.013 --> 39:40.681
I swear on my life

39:40.683 --> 39:43.317
this is Rosmund,

39:43.319 --> 39:46.687
daughter of the king!

39:46.689 --> 39:48.689
Hail to the queen!

